  "description": "A classic household two-chamber refrigerator, primarily notable for its support for the No Frost technology to prevent ice and frost from forming on the walls of the chambers, reliable inverter compressors and separate cooling circuits for the working chambers. The model was introduced to the market by the popular LG brand in 2023 and is positioned by the manufacturer in the mid-price segment. The total useful capacity of the model is 344 liters. The refrigeration compartment boasts a Door Cooling additional blowing system for the door opening, which allows you to quickly equalize the temperature when opening the refrigerator door. The Multi Air Flow system is used for the most even distribution of cold across the drawers and shelves. The two-chamber refrigerator LG GB-V3100CPY is equipped with a capacious Moist Balance Crisper vegetable drawer. Additionally, a container with a Fresh Converter freshness zone is provided. The capacity of the freezer located below is 110 liters. The refrigeration unit uses an insulated body that can be safely pushed close to walls or furniture. This model has two circulation circuits, and the refrigerant is pumped by a quiet and efficient inverter compressor. The compressor is covered by an official LG 10-year warranty. The refrigeration system operates at a volume of up to 35 dB.",
